Sparta Rotterdam goalkeeper, Maduka Okoye, will be hoping to earn his sixth clean sheet of the season when they face Heerenveen on Sunday (today) in a Dutch Eredivisie game, PUNCH Sports Extra reports. Okoye who was named in the Dutch Eredivisie’s Team of The Month for March having kept three clean sheets for Sparta in the month under review has kept five clean sheets so far this term conceding 29 goals in 21 league appearances for Sparta Rotterdam. The Eredivisie’s Team of The Month had three FC Twente players two from Ajax and PSV while Go Ahead Eagles, AZ Alkmaar and Groningen had one player respectively. Aside’s Okoye, the players who made the Eredivisie team of the month are Philipp Max (PSV), Julio Pleguezuelo (FC Twente), Robin Propper (FC Twente), Joshua Brenet (FC Twente), Ryan Gravenberch (Ajax), Luuk Brouwers (Go Ahead Eagles), Jesper Karlsson (AZ), Michael de Leeuw (FC Groningen), Sébastien Haller (Ajax) and Eran Zahavi (PSV). Okoye who missed Nigeria’s playoff game against Ghana after contracting COVID-19 last week. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com